SEARCH

All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Athlete
The Athlete class represents a Futsal player in the game.
AthleteGenerator
The AthleteGenerator Class is used to randomly generate Athletes to be used in the game.
ClubScreen
ClubScreen class.
DefenceTrainingEquipment
An Item that increases an Athlete's defence stat.
DefensiveCoach
An Item that increases an Athlete's defence stat.
EndScreen
This is the final screen of the game and it is opened at the end of the season.
GameManager
Game Manager class.
InsaneFood
An Item that increases an Athlete's stamina stat.
InventoryScreen
The Inventory page is where the player can view and use Items they have bought from the Market.
Item
The Item class reprents the Purchasables at the Market which are not Athletes.
MainScreen
This class represents the main screen of the game, which connects most of the other screens together.
MarketScreen
The screen that displays Athletes and Items for sale and allows the player to make purchases/sales.
MarketSellScreen
A variation of the Market that enables selling of items instead of purchases.
Match
This class represents a Match between the player's team and another team of Athletes.
MatchGenerator
The MatchGenerator class handles the random generation of Matches to be shown in the StadiumScreen.
MatchScreen
This is the screen that displays the outcome of a Match and the individual Athlete faceoffs that constitute a Match.
Nutritionist
An Item that increases an Athlete's health stat.
OffenceTrainingEquipment
An Item that increases an Athlete's offence stat.
OffensiveCoach
An Item that increases an Athlete's offence stat.
Purchasable
The Purchasable interface describes objects which can be purchased or sold from the Market.
RandomEvent
The RandomEvent class represents, generates and handles a RandomEvent.
SetupScreen
This is the screen that opens immediately after the start screen.
StadiumScreen
This screen presents the player with a list of available Matches to play and shows their total season points earned thus far.
StartScreen
This is the screen that opens when the game starts, it's a simple title screen with a start button that takes you to the next screen.
Trainer
An Item that increases an Athlete's stamina stat.
TrainingScreen
The TrainingScreen opens whenever the player takes a bye.
